        "keyFindings": [
          "Battery price spreads across major European markets saw a significant upward trend in March 2026, with Poland and Germany reaching 7-day average peaks above 200 €/MWh.",
          "Daily volatility was extreme in early March, with individual daily spikes in some markets exceeding 300 €/MWh.",
          "Great Britain (GB) consistently exhibited the lowest spreads among the group, rarely exceeding 100 €/MWh even during the March peak.",
          "The spreads in Italy and Spain were more moderate compared to Central European markets like Germany and Poland but still followed the general upward trend in March.",
          "By late March and early April, spreads began to converge and stabilize between 100 and 150 €/MWh for most continental European markets."
        ],
